## ConstParamTy on UFixed / IFixed

UFixed and IFixed do NOT derive ConstParamTy in round 202604500000.
Required when a consumer wants `const X: UFixed<...>` const-generic
positions. Today no consumer surface needs this; aliases live at
use-sites only.

Lift requires resolving the associated-type-projection cascade in
`<S as UContainerFor<N>>::T` field positions (the Bits inner type
through UFixed's `bits: Bits<{ufixed_bits(I,F)}, S>` field). Verified-
friction on rustc 1.96-nightly (fda6d37bb 2026-03-27):
core::marker::ConstParamTy is derive-macro-only at this rustc
version, and using it as a trait bound on UContainerFor::T is
non-trivial. The derive-macro path may work directly on UFixed /
IFixed once the cascade is established; verify when a consumer
need lands.

Constraints from prior design-review prose corrections:

- The cascade requirement applies only to const-generic params
  (I: IBits, F: FBits). The S type parameter is a marker type, not
  a const value.
- A `_phantom: PhantomData<S>` field is redundant with the
  `bits: Bits<..., S>` field carrying S. Do not add it on lift.
- Auto-trait inheritance from S is preserved without function-pointer
  phantom hacks (Strategy markers are unit structs and trivially
  Send/Sync).

## Semantic domain aliases (researched widths)

Shipped by polka-dots; dropped from arvo L0 per doc CL D1 (consumer
concern). Each width was chosen deliberately; when a consumer
re-introduces one, these are the researched defaults. Names are
written unquoted so the design-doc lint does not treat them as
backticked types.

| Alias     |  I |  F | Rationale                                           |
|-----------|---:|---:|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Ratio     |  0 |  8 | pure fractional [0, 1) — probabilities, weights     |
| Factor    |  2 |  8 | [0, 4) range — multipliers, scale factors           |
| Norm      |  1 | 14 | signed [-1, 1) — normalised eigenvector components  |
| Angle     |  9 |  7 | 512+ directions, sub-degree precision               |
| Coord     | 16 | 16 | ±65k range with sub-pixel precision                 |
| Count     | 32 |  0 | row / element counts                                |
| Average   | 16 | 16 | symmetric precision for means of coordinates        |
| Deviation |  8 | 24 | mostly fractional — variance components             |
| Bool      |  1 |  0 | single-bit; stays Hot (no precision to lose)        |

Default strategy `Warm` in consumer code, except `Bool` which stays
`Hot`. Source: polka-dots loimu-primitives.

## Deferred newtypes

Decided to live in consuming layers, not L0:

- ByteCount — `u64` wrapping byte counts. Belongs where memory sizing
  happens (column storage layer / arena engine).
- Alignment — power-of-two alignment value. Belongs at the storage
  boundary.
- CoreCount — small-int CPU core count. Platform-environment; lives
  adjacent to `ThreadPool`.
- Nanoseconds — `u64` nanosecond count. Lives adjacent to `Clock`.

No written rationale for specific widths survived into polka-dots
design docs; pick per-consumer as needs arise.

## Cross-width and cross-strategy arithmetic

The L0 implementation ships same-strategy same-width arithmetic only.
Cross-width (different I / F between operands) and cross-strategy
(different S between operands) `Add` / `Sub` / `Mul` / `Div` impls
are blocked on `generic_const_exprs` support for `max()` in const
arguments and const-expression projection over associated types on
current nightly. Deferred to a later round when the const evaluator
catches up or an alternative encoding surfaces.

## Numeric trait impls deferred beyond L0

- `Sqrt` / `Recip` for fractional `UFixed` / `IFixed` need
